ction)\n28\t  - `data/kp_metrics.json` (new — append-only metrics)\n29\t  - `data/kp_validation_log.csv` (new — human review decisions)\n30\t- Result: Pipeline runs successfully. 50-lead test: Stage 2 found 4 direct contacts (10.8% rate), Stage 3 auto-approved 2, auto-rejected name-only candidates, 5 sent to human review.\n31\t- Achievements:\n32\t  - Stage 2 sitemap parsing eliminates most 404s from URL guessing.\n33\t  - Stage 3 scoring correctly rejects name-only candidates (no email/phone/LinkedIn).\n34\t  - Company emails (info@, hello@) penalized in scoring.\n35\t  - LinkedIn URL search and extraction integrated.\n36\t  - Multi-contact extraction from team pages added.\n37\t  - Random delay between requests to reduce rate-limiting.\n38\t  - Pipeline reports consolidated in `reports/kp-pipeline/`.\n39\t- Issues / limits:\n40\t  - Google dork searches frequently return 429 rate-limit. Primary value comes from direct page scraping, not Google search.\n41\t  - Team pages often list names without emails/LinkedIn — multi-contact extraction depends on pages having actual contact data.\n42\t  - No human review data accumulated yet — automation gates (false_positive_rate < 15%, auto_approve_accuracy > 95%) cannot be evaluated.\n43\t- Follow-up: User to review Stage 3 candidates via dashboard, export decisions. Accumulate validation data to evaluate automation gates. Consider Tavily API to replace Google search if 429 persists.\n44\t\n45\t## 2026-05-15 - Fix Hidden Persistent Notification Launch\n46\t\n47\t## 2026-05-15 - Fix Hidden Persistent Notification Launch\n48\t\n49\t- User request: Diagnose why the notification popup did not appear in a new window even though notifications worked elsewhere.\n50\t- Handling plan: Compare global and project hook launch paths against direct popup tests, identify hidden-window launch flags, remove them only from visible persistent popup paths, keep silent flags for background MCP/toast helpers, and verify with manual launcher/hook s